cde_info: Sex is defined as A textual description of a person's sex at birth. Its values are Male|Female|Intersex|None of these describe me|Prefer not to answer|Unknown.

Sex at Birth is defined as The physical sexual characteristics of the neonate at birth. A textual description of a person's sex at birth. Its values are Female|Male|Intersex|None of these describe me|Prefer not to answer.
Sex is defined as Self-identified gender where gender is the assemblage of properties that distinguish people on the basis of the societal roles. Its values are 1|2|3.
Sex values are 1|2.
Sex at Birth is defined as The self-reported sex of the participant/subject at birth. Its values are Other Not Listed|Undifferentiated/Indeterminate/Intersex|Male|Female|Declined to Answer/Unknown.
Sex of Participant is defined as Used by the registry to generate the GUID. Its values are None.

Sex type is defined as The sex of the subject/participant. Its values are Male|Female.

Sex [AHRQ] is defined as The patient's documented sex (gender) on arrival at the hospital. This term was created for the "Patient gender" data element on the Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality (AHRQ) Healthcare Event Reporting Form (HERF), version 1.2. [https://ushik.ahrq.gov/ViewItemDetails?&system=mdr&itemKey=169064000&enableAsynchronousLoading=true]. Its values are a|b|c.
Sex type code is defined as Code for the subject/participant's sex. Its values are 1|2.

Sex of Family member is defined as Sex of a family member, including sibling, parent, child, or other family member. To specify the family member relation, use Relationship to patient [LOINC: 54136-7]. Its values are Male|Female|Other.
Sex [USSG-FHT] is defined as Sex of the patient, created for the U.S. Surgeon General's Family Health History Portrait. Its values are Male|Female|Other.

Societal sex is defined as This term was created for the U.S. Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) 2015 Edition Health Information Technology (Health IT) Certification Criteria final rule. [https://www.federalregister.gov/articles/2015/10/16/2015-25597/2015-edition-health-information-technology-health-it-certification-criteria-2015-edition-base]. Its values are Male|Female|Unknown.

Animal sex type is defined as Type of animal species sex as determined by observation. Its values are 2|1|444.

Sex genotype type is defined as The difference between male and female, based upon the interactions between genes and between the genotype and the environment. Genotype is identified based on the individual's reproductive organs and functions assigned by chromosomal complement. Its values are XX|XY|XXX|XYY|XXY|Other, specify|Unknown|Unspecified.
Birth sex assigned type is defined as Self-reported phenotypic sex of participant/subject, assigned at birth. Its values are Male|Female|Intersex|Unknown|Other, specify.

Sexual Compulsivity (SCS) - sex thought strong than self scale is defined as I feel that sexual thoughts and feelings are stronger than I am. As part of Sexual Compulsivity Scale (SCS) questionnaire. Its values are 1|2|3|4.

Parent gender type is defined as Self-reported gender of the participant's/subject's parent. Gender is the socially constructed identity of sex. Gender is equated with phenotypic sex. Gender may differ from the sex of a parent determined genetically. Its values are Female|Male|Unknown|Unspecified|Not reported.
In the past 30 days How much has a medical device (for example, port, colostomy bag, or oxygen tank) affected your satisfaction with your sex life? values are 0|1|2|3|4|5.
Family history gender type is defined as Reported gender of the relative. Gender is the socially constructed identity of sex. Its values are Female|Male.
Sibling gender type is defined as Reported gender of the sibling. Gender is the socially constructed identity of sex. Its values are Female|Male|Unknown|Unspecified|Not reported.

How many times in the last year have you contributed to the delinquency of a person under age 17 [Denver Youth Survey] is defined as That is, you helped them to run away, gave them alcohol or drugs, or had sex with them. Its values are numbers.

Gender identity type is defined as Gender identity self-identified by the subject/participant. Gender type may or may not match sex assigned at birth. Its values are Male|Female|Unknown|Other, specify.

Family History Research Diagnostic Criteria (FH-RDC) - Gender type code is defined as Code denoting the sex of the selected relative of the participant/subject, as part of the Family History - Research Diagnostic Criteria (FH-RDC). Its values are 1|2.

Gender is defined as Characteristics of people that are socially constructed, including norms, behaviors, and roles based on sex. As a social construct, gender varies from society to society and can change over time. (Adapted from WHO.). Its values are Man|Woman|Non-Binary|Transgender|None of these describe me.  I would like to consider additional options|Prefer not to answer.

Gender - Select Other is defined as Additional Options for characteristics of people that are socially constructed, including norms, behaviors, and roles based on sex. As a social construct, gender varies from society to society and can change over time. (Adapted from WHO.). Its values are Trans man / Transgender Man/ FTM|Trans Woman / Transgender Woman / MTF|Genderqueer|Genderfluid|Gender Variant|Questioning or unsure of your gender identity|None of these describe me, and I want to specify.

Tanner stage is defined as Stages of physical development in children, adolescents and adults. The scale defines physical measurements of development based on external primary and secondary sex characteristics, such as the size of the breasts, genitalia, and development of pubic hair. Its values are I|II|III|IV|V.

Questionnaire for Impulsive-Compulsive Disorders in Parkinson's Disease (QUIP) - difficult control indicator is defined as Indicator of whether the participant has difficulty controlling his or her impulsive behaviors toward gambling, sex, buying, or eating, as part of the Questionnaire for Impulsive-Compulsive Disorders in Parkinson's Disease (QUIP). Its values are No|Yes.

Questionnaire for Impulsive-Compulsive Disorders in Parkinson's Disease (QUIP) - impulse control disorder indicator is defined as Indicator of whether the participant believes that he or she has an impulsive control disorder to engage in gambling, sex, buying, or eating, as part of the Questionnaire for Impulsive-Compulsive Disorders in Parkinson's Disease (QUIP). Its values are No|Yes.

Tanner stage genitalia scale is defined as The scale defining physical measurements of development based on external primary and secondary sex characteristics, such as the size of the breasts, genitalia, and development of pubic hair to characterize stages of physical development in children, adolescents and adults. Its values are I|II|III|IV|V.

Tanner stage pubic hair scale is defined as The scale defining physical measurements of development based on external primary and secondary sex characteristics, such as the size of the breasts, genitalia, and development of pubic hair to characterize stages of physical development in children, adolescents and adults. Its values are I|II|III|IV|V.

Gender - Specify is defined as Other - My gender identification is not a listed option for characteristics of people that are socially constructed, including norms, behaviors, and roles based on sex. As a social construct, gender varies from society to society and can change over time. (Adapted from WHO.). Its values are text.

Questionnaire for Impulsive-Compulsive Disorders in Parkinson's Disease (QUIP) - guilty trouble mind indicator is defined as Indicator of whether the participant believes that he or she has trouble keeping gambling, sex, buying, or eating out of the mind or feels guilty about the thoughts, as part of the Questionnaire for Impulsive-Compulsive Disorders in Parkinson's Disease (QUIP). Its values are No|Yes.

PhenX - family conflict - intimate-relationship protocol 210401 is defined as The Revised Conflict Tactics Scales (CTS 2) is a 78-item, self-administered questionnaire that assesses both positive and negative behaviors used in response to conflict between romantic partners in the past year. The Revised Conflict Tactics Scales (CTS 2) is a proprietary instrument, and administration requires a licensing agreement from Western Psychological Services. Romantic partners are defined as any two adult individuals engaged in an intimate relationship, including both married and unmarried partners and both same-sex and opposite-sex partners. Its values are text.

Questionnaire for Impulsive-Compulsive Disorders in Parkinson's Disease (QUIP) - activity continue behavior indicator is defined as Indicator of whether the participant engages in activities (hiding what you are doing, lying, hoarding, borrowing, accumulating debt, stealing, or other illegal acts) to continue gambling, sex, buying, or eating, as part of the Questionnaire for Impulsive-Compulsive Disorders in Parkinson's Disease (QUIP). Its values are No|Yes.

Creatinine Clearance Result (mL/min) is defined as A measurement of kidney function typically estimated from the blood creatinine level in addition to other factors such as race, age, gender and weight, expressed as milliliters per minute. Normal values vary depending on age, sex, and body weight but it is typically > 80 milliliters per minute (mL/min). Its values are numbers.

Questionnaire for Impulsive-Compulsive Disorders in Parkinson's Disease (QUIP) - impulse control disorder type is defined as Types of impulse control disorders, as part of the Questionnaire for Impulsive-Compulsive Disorders in Parkinson's Disease (QUIP). Its values are Gambling|Sex|Buying|Eating.
Neuroendocrine lab panel type is defined as The type of specific neuroendocrine lab panel that was performed. Its values are Cortisol|Diabetes|Thyroid|Sex hormones|Other.

Sexual Orientation is defined as The pattern of a person's emotional, romantic, and/or sexual attractions. Its values are Lesbian|Gay|Straight, that is, not gay or lesbian, etc.|Bisexual|None of these describe me, and I'd like to see additional options.
